### OSI Layer 1 (Physical)
The Physical layer is responsible for transmitting raw bits over a physical medium. In this lab, cables, ports, and powered devices represent Layer 1.

### OSI Layer 2 (Data Link)
Switches use MAC addresses to forward frames within the local network.

![MAC Table](mac-table.png)

### OSI Layer 3 (Network)
Routers use IP addressing and routing tables to forward packets between networks.

