## Part 2 – Protocol Security (OSI Layers 4–7)

### TCP vs UDP
TCP uses a three-way handshake (SYN, SYN-ACK, ACK), making it more secure and reliable. UDP is connectionless and faster but less secure.

### HTTP vs HTTPS
HTTPS uses TLS/SSL encryption to protect data, while HTTP sends data in plaintext.

![HTTP vs HTTPS](http-https.png)

### SSH vs Telnet
SSH encrypts remote sessions, while Telnet sends data in cleartext.

![SSH](ssh.png)

